radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated measuring 12 mm with hyperemia and surrounding fat stranding consistent with acute appendicitis. There is mild thickening of the base of the cecum, likely reactive. Bases of the lungs are clear. Unremarkable visualized heart and pericardium. The liver enhances homogeneously without focal lesions. The pancreas, spleen, and adrenal glands are unremarkable. Kidneys show symmetric nephrograms and excretion of contrast without lesions. No lymph node enlargement. Stomach collapsed. Small bowel unremarkable with no obstruction. Uterus normal size with heterogeneous masses likely representing fibroids. No pelvic free fluid.
